<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Apparently rare localised to western Panama and Costa Rica in moist hill forest around 1800-2000 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">PANAMA.</emphasis>
Chiriqui: Nueva Suissa, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T.B. Croat</emphasis>
13504 (MO).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">COSTA RICA.</emphasis>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Tonduz</emphasis>
11701 (MO). San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="José">Jose</normalizedToken>
, Cordillera de Talamanca, Copey de Dota, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M.M. Chavarria</emphasis>
1069 (K, MO).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is characterised by the long-peduncled, few-flowered cymes of white flowers with broad oblong-ovate, mucronate, mostly scarious inner sepals.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
